properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 9 at 1:07PM PST until February 9 at 11:33PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Snohomish River At Snohomish affecting Snohomish County
Cedar River Near Landsburg affecting King County
Cedar River At Renton affecting King County

...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...
Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County
Green River Near Auburn affecting King County
White River At R Street Bridge affecting King and Pierce Counties


Dry conditions will persist today and Monday allowing for river levels
to continue to recede.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Snoqualmie River Near Carnation
* Until this evening.
* At 12:15 PM Sunday the stage was 53.7 feet.
* Flood stage is 54.0 feet.
* Fell below flood stage late this morning.
* No additional flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river fell below flood stage at 10:39 AM Sunday and
will continue to fall. Flooding will continue in some areas until
the flood wave has completely passed downstream.
* Impact...At 51.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will spill over its
banks from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall...with
shallow water over some farm land and several roads.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
